item.title: Get it off your chest #2!
item.dc:creator: @Yz85Racer Yz85Racer
item.description:
@Yz85Racer wrote:

Aight I’ll take part in this thread.

I am not sure what to do anymore. 3 weeks I had the worst crash of my life/many had seen before. 2nd corner I landed from a jump awkwardly, and got thrown over the handlebars violently head first… only to be run over 4 times by other riders landing on me… And about a minute later was hit again in the side of the head as I was crawling too the side of the track, this knocked me out for 10 minutes.

Considering how violent of a crash it was, and the lack of serious injuries I have, I think it’s safe to say I dodged a bullet. Final injuries are; 5 fractured ribs, kidney/liver bruising, spleen was pushed out of place by about 2cm, compressed T3-4 vertebrae, broken scaphoid, and muscle damage around my spine… if you look at my back, the muscles that run parallel too your spine… mine are pushed out at my T3-4 vertebrae l0l.

Still, the worst experience of it all… was the catheter.
